Sentencas: This work evaluates the effects of the sintering temperature (800 degrees C, 900 degrees C, 1000 degrees C) of SrTi1-xFexO3-delta (x = 0.35, 0.5, 0.7) porous electrodes on their electrochemical performance as potential oxygen electrode materials of solid oxide cells.
Titulo: Effect of sintering temperature on electrochemical performance of porous SrTi1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.35, 0.5, 0.7) oxygen electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The materials were prepared by a solid-state reaction method and revealed the expected cubic perovskite structure.
Titulo: Effect of sintering temperature on electrochemical performance of porous SrTi1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.35, 0.5, 0.7) oxygen electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: After milling, the powders were characterised by a sub-micrometre particle size with high sinter-activity.
Titulo: Effect of sintering temperature on electrochemical performance of porous SrTi1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.35, 0.5, 0.7) oxygen electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: It was shown that the lowest area specific resistance was achieved after sintering SrTi0.65Fe0.35O3 electrodes at 1000 degrees C, and SrTi0.5Fe0.5O3 and SrTi0.30Fe0.70O3 electrodes at 800 degrees C, which can be considered to be a relatively low temperature.
Titulo: Effect of sintering temperature on electrochemical performance of porous SrTi1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.35, 0.5, 0.7) oxygen electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: In general, EIS measurements showed that increasing the Fe content results in lowered electrode polarisation and a decrease of the series resistance.
Titulo: Effect of sintering temperature on electrochemical performance of porous SrTi1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.35, 0.5, 0.7) oxygen electrodes for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Even though the studied materials have much lower total conductivities than state-of-the-art electrode materials (e.g. (La,Sr)(Co,Fe)O-3), the polarisation resistances obtained in this work can be considered low.
Titulo: Effect of sintering temperature on electrochemical performance of porous SrTi1-xFexO3-δ (x=0.35, 0.5, 0.7) oxygen electrodes for solid oxide cells
